The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The paper also discusses information theory and sketching, which are relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of lower bounds and upper bounds for functions suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the study of communication complexity with imperfectly shared randomness falls under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
